 1990-25201990-11-220OLD INAC,  ,  ,  , 
PrecisOrder which provides for: (a) the approval of the terms and the signature of a SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT between the Gov't of Canada and the Gov't of Saskatchewan pertaining to the partial settlement of outstanding treaty land entitlements (Treaty No. 6) of the FLYING DUST BAND; (b) the setting apart of some 97.8 hectares of land situate in the vicinity of Jarvis Lake for the use and benefit of that band as GLADUE LAKE INDIAN RESERVE NO. 105B; and (c) the exercise by Saskatchewan of its powers to establish a right-of-way across the reserve for public roadway purposes.
